			<outline text="August 15" type="calendarDay" name="15" >
				<outline text="I just added eleven questions to &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.harvard.edu/doc/2021/08/15/beyond-the-web/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; toward making clear what can't be done on the Web for architectural reasons, but can be done through alternative designs." type="tweet" created="Sun, 15 Aug 2021 21:59:41 GMT" tweetId="1427027241310072833" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1427027241310072833" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="We need to start thinking and working outside the Web's haystack: &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.harvard.edu/doc/2021/08/15/beyond-the-web/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/KIqv2hJ4Bv" type="tweet" created="Sun, 15 Aug 2021 16:18:18 GMT" tweetId="1426941328752001027" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1426941328752001027" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Beyond the Web &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.harvard.edu/doc/2021/08/15/beyond-the-web/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 15 Aug 2021 16:13:30 GMT" tweetId="1426940119991431169" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1426940119991431169" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="This is important, folks. Pay attention. (You're already  overpaying for homes because of this kind of stuff.) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/RealEstateCafe/status/1426662367098810374&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 15 Aug 2021 02:34:09 GMT" tweetId="1426733925246853122" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1426733925246853122" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
