			<outline text="August 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="My answer to a @quora question about bad radio reception in a city: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.quora.com/Why-doesnt-radio-reception-work-am-FM-on-a-radio-I-live-in-a-large-city-with-many-radio-stations-In-my-apartment-most-of-the-stations-come-in-with-heavy-static-Should-I-connect-my-radio-to-an-external-antenna&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 20:18:17 GMT" tweetId="1423015456273797129" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1423015456273797129" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="1/2 WTF is with @Quora? Based on awful algorithmic inference, presumably, it suggested in an email that I might like the Biden Lies &quot;space.&quot; On the bottom of the email I clcked on the &quot;mute Biden Lies&quot; link and it sent me there anyway, with this: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422354605170647044/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 00:32:18 GMT" tweetId="1422354605170647044" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422354605170647044" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" >
					<outline text="2/2 I get @quora wanting some soc-med action, but as a strategic and branding move, this is about as wrong as wrong gets. (BTW &amp;amp; FWIW, the email came from what presented as Quora Suggested Spaces with the address biden-lies@quora.com.)" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 00:36:57 GMT" tweetId="1422355775817662467" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422355775817662467" inReplyToId="1422354605170647044" tweetUserName="dsearls" >
						<outline text="Just did this: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422361486249414658/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 00:59:39 GMT" tweetId="1422361486249414658" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422361486249414658" inReplyToId="1422355775817662467" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="My answer to a question in @quora about radio and politics: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.quora.com/Should-radio-stations-not-only-cater-to-an-audience-but-to-go-far-as-to-partner-with-a-partison-political-group-too-While-I-agree-that-a-radio-station-should-cater-to-their-audience-I-think-that-it-goes-too-far-when/answer/Doc-Searls&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 22:40:05 GMT" tweetId="1422326362887569415" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422326362887569415" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Car design trends &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.harvard.edu/doc/2021/08/02/car-design-trends/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 18:34:44 GMT" tweetId="1422264618794340352" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1422264618794340352" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
