			<outline text="July 18" type="calendarDay" name="18" >
				<outline text="What is the difference between &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/home&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; behind the bird and behind the bird house? I know they bring somewhat different results when one clicks on them, but how I'm not sure. The obvious isn't always apparent to me." type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 18:18:10 GMT" tweetId="1416824634864017415" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1416824634864017415" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Been here in interspace for several decades now, but this is the first time I've seen this one in my location bar when I copied a text string I wanted to search. Makes me think: if you don't want your text copied, don't put it in the world's biggest copy machine. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1416723010896150535/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 11:34:21 GMT" tweetId="1416723010896150535" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1416723010896150535" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
